NonMetricSpaceLib::::.appveyor.yml::::install::::install_6::::cmd::::ECHO Platform : %PLATFORM%
ECHO Python : %PYTHON%
ECHO PATH : %PATH%
dir "C:\"
python --version
python -m pip --version

NonMetricSpaceLib::::.appveyor.yml::::build_script::::build_script_1::::cmd::::python -m pip install -qq -r requirements.txt
python setup.py build_ext
python -m pip install -U .

NonMetricSpaceLib::::.appveyor.yml::::deploy_script::::deploy_script_0::::ps::::if ($env:APPVEYOR_REPO_TAG -ne "true") {
  echo "Skipping deployment because this is not a tagged commit"
  return
}
# Specify account details for PyPI
echo "Deploying..."
mv .pypirc $env:USERPROFILE\\.pypirc
# Workaround required to ensure setup.py finds the .pypirc under Windows
$env:HOME=$env:USERPROFILE
# Install wheel-building support
python -m pip install --user wheel twine
# Build wheel and upload
cd python_bindings
python setup.py build_ext
python setup.py sdist bdist_wheel
python -m twine upload -r pypi -p $env:pypipassword --skip-existing dist/*
echo "Deployment complete"

NonMetricSpaceLib::::.travis.yml::::before_install::::PY=python
echo "TRAVIS_OS_NAME=$TRAVIS_OS_NAME"
echo "PYTHON=$PYTHON"
if [ "$TRAVIS_OS_NAME" = "linux" ]; then 
  export CXX=g++ CC=gcc
  if [ $(echo "$PYTHON" | grep "^3\.") ]; then
    echo "bootstrapping pip module"
    PY=python${PYTHON}
    # For older PYTHON need a separate script or else it may fail
    if [ "$PYTHON" = "3.5" ] ; then
      GET_PIP_SCRIPT="https://bootstrap.pypa.io/pip/3.5/get-pip.py"
    else
      GET_PIP_SCRIPT="https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py"
    fi
    echo "Using PIP bootstrapping script $GET_PIP_SCRIPT"
    curl  "$GET_PIP_SCRIPT" | sudo -H $PY
  fi
fi

if [[ "$TRAVIS_OS_NAME" == "osx" ]]; then
  pyenv install $PYTHON
  PY=/Users/travis/.pyenv/versions/${PYTHON}/bin/python
fi

PIP="$PY -m pip"
if [ "$PYTHON" = "2.7" ] ; then
  echo "Keeping an old pip version for Python$PYTHON"
  sudo -H $PIP install --upgrade "pip < 21.0"
else
  sudo -H $PIP install --upgrade pip
fi

NonMetricSpaceLib::::.travis.yml::::install::::if [ "$TRAVIS_OS_NAME" = "linux" ]; then
  cmake similarity_search -DWITH_EXTRAS=1
else
  cmake similarity_search
fi
make -j 4
$PIP install --user scipy six flake8 psutil
cd python_bindings
$PIP install --user -r requirements.txt
$PY setup.py build_ext
$PIP install --user .
cd ..

NonMetricSpaceLib::::.travis.yml::::script::::if [ "$TRAVIS_OS_NAME" = "linux" ] ; then
    set -e
    cd similarity_search;
    ./release/bunit
    travis_retry ./release/test_integr integr.log 
    cd ..
    set +e
fi

NonMetricSpaceLib::::.travis.yml::::after_script::::if [ "$TRAVIS_TAG" ]; then
  export TRAVIS_OS_NAME
  export PY
  export PIP
  export PYTHON
  bash travis/deploy.sh
  $PIP install --user "six>=1.9.0"
  $PIP install --user twine
  cp .pypirc ~/.pypirc
  pwd
  ls python_bindings/
  ls python_bindings/dist/
  $PY -m twine upload -r pypi -p $PYPI_PASSWORD --skip-existing python_bindings/dist/* &>/dev/null
  echo "Twine upload status: $?"
else
  echo "Skipping deployment because this is not a tagged commit"
fi
